1. Conformity to societal norms suggests the behavior is acceptable and widespread.
2. The phrase "everybody does it" implies universality and normalcy of the behavior.
3. The behavior is seen as part of the social fabric and not something to be condemned.
4. The statement implies that the behavior is common enough to be considered normal.
5. The speaker is pointing out the hypocrisy or double standard in condemning the behavior when it is so widespread.